Volkswagen is a German automaker founded on 28 May 1937 by the German Labour Front, and headquartered
in Wolfsburg. It is the flagship marque of the Volkswagen Group, the largest automaker by worldwide sales
in 2016 and 2017. The group's main market is in China, which delivers 40% of its sales and profits.

Volkswagen translates to "people's car" in German. The company's current international advertising slogan
is just "Volkswagen", referencing the name's meaning.